' ============================================================
' NOTES
' ============================================================

note top of UCValidJwt
  JWT Bearer middleware — cross-cutting.
  Every request except /health and
  Group 0 anonymous endpoints (login, refresh,
  forgot-password, reset-password) passes
  through JWT validation.
  tenant_id is derived from the JWT claim —
  NEVER trusted from client headers or body.
  Replaces the Phase 1 ApiKeyMiddleware.
end note

note right of UCPolicy
  Four policies:
  - SuperAdminOnly       → DELETE /users/{id}
  - CpAdminOrAbove       → /users CRUD, /identity/override
  - TenantMember         → /devices, /events, /audit, /dashboard
  - CanExecuteCommands   → /commands/*, /devices/{id}/{move|label|approve|reject}
end note

note right of UCWazuhAlerts
  Phase 2 — requires Wazuh Manager deployed.
  WazuhApiClient is registered in DI only when
  Wazuh:Enabled = true.
end note

note bottom of UCExec
  ASYNC path. Option D per call:
  - CommandEndpoints → CommandDispatcherBase subclass
  - Subclass acquires its own HubConnection,
    registers its own .On<string>() handler,
    invokes, awaits (cts-bounded), disposes.
  - No shared _pending dictionary.
  - 409 Conflict only on same-device + same-dispatcher
    in-flight (enforced by AcquireAdminConnectionAsync
    + dispatcher-scoped gate).
  - 504 on timeout, 503 on hub disconnect, 404 on
    cross-tenant device lookup.
end note

note bottom of UCListDev
  All Group 3 queries are tenant-scoped through
  IActorContext.TenantId. For CpAdmin/SuperAdmin
  the tenant_id is null → repository treats that
  as "all tenants" — handled inside the repo, not
  the endpoint. See TenantContext change in 05B §5B.5.
end note

note top of UCBootstrap
  Ran once by BootstrapUserSeeder at startup.
  If controlit_users is empty, creates SuperAdmin
  from CONTROLIT_BOOTSTRAP_EMAIL / _PASSWORD with
  must_change_password = true.
  Missing env vars on first run → fail fast + loud.
end note

